immigrate /ˈɪmɪˌɡreɪt/

(immigrating,immigrated,immigrates) 

1. V-I If someone immigrates to a particular country, they come to live or work in that country, after leaving the country where they were born. 移居国外; 移民 [no passive] 

例： ...a Russian-born professor who had immigrated to the United States. ...一位生于俄罗斯而后来移居到美国的教授。 

例： He immigrated from India at age 

18. 他18岁时从印度移民出来。 

